my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, lifejacket, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if necessary; 
c) Trip hazards and any overhead obstructions to be clearly marked; 
d) All steps, platforms and deck surface should be clear of any oil and / or grease residue; 
e) The decks must have unhindered access; 
f) The crew should not be required to leave the protection of the vessel's safety rails - A life line or safety harness should be worn if there is any risk of falling.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Lifejackets should never be worn during launching of free-fall lifeboat; 
c) All the crew which is in inside the Free Fall Lifeboat should remove helmets once inside of it to avoid neck/back injuries.

a) All crew must be trained and have a full understanding with regard to the launch / recovery of free-fall lifeboat, including the release mechanism; 
b) Ensure there is sufficient depth of water for launching; 
c) Check and remove any obstructions i.e. under the lifeboat, in the water, on the boat deck; 
d) All crew should embark, sit in the assigned seats and fasten the seatbelts as soon as seated; 
e) Ensure all hatches and vents are tightly closed.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, lifejacket, etc.; 
b) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
c) Consult 'SOLAS Training Manual', if necessary.

a) All crew must be trained and have a full understanding with regard to the launch / recovery of free-fall lifeboat, including release mechanism; 
b) Consult 'SOLAS Training Manual'; 
c) Maintenance and inspections to be carried out in accordance with the Manufacturer's Manual and Company MPM system; 
d) Ensure all securing devices are engaged when carrying out maintenance; 
e) Ensure all release hooks are engaged prior to embarkation; 
f) On recovery, ensure that the recovery hooks are engaged properly.

a) Maintenance and inspections to be carried out in accordance with the Manufacturer's Manual and Company MPM system; 
b) The lifting wires should be visually inspected and condition checked regularly; 
c) Wires found in poor condition or damaged must be replaced immediately; 
d) The release / recovery hooks, including safety latch and springs should be visually inspected and condition checked regularly; 
e) Ensure all lashing devices are removed prior to launching.
